news.title: Delhi master plan 2041 may be sent back to drawing board
news.para: Delhi's Master Plan 2041, designed to guide the capital's urban development, is under review by the Delhi government after being submitted to the Centre in April 2023. The Delhi government held a closed-door meeting to review various provisions of the document.

news.title: Elan group raises ₹250 crore from Piramal Finance
news.para: Elan Group, a Gurgaon-based developer, has secured Rs 250 crore from Piramal Finance. The funding will support the construction of a commercial project in Gurgaon. This follows a Rs 1,200 crore funding from Kotak Real Estate Fund last year. Elan Group will use the funds to expedite its regional projects. The company's portfolio includes 15 projects across various segments.

news.title: Lucknow development body orders probe into unauthorised construction
news.para: The Lucknow Development Authority is investigating unauthorized construction in Gomtinagar's Vinamra Khand, prompted by a neighbor's complaints. Yamini Mathur alleges violations of the approved building plan, including encroachment on setback areas.

news.title: After 16 years, Gujarat drafts new policy to boost township projects
news.para: Gujarat is overhauling its urban housing strategy with a new township policy, aiming to incentivize organized and affordable housing. The revised policy addresses shortcomings of the 2009 version by offering incentives like relaxed FSI and tax breaks. It also ensures better alignment with urban development plans to attract real estate developers for large-scale, self-sustained townships.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body receives 49,000 suggestions & objections to its draft of revised development plan
news.para: Pimpri Chinchwad Municipal Corporation finished taking suggestions for the revised development plan. They received 49,000 responses from residents. A committee will review these submissions. The draft plan was earlier approved on May 16. Residents and politicians opposed road networks and amenity reservations. Objections were raised against the High Capacity Mass Transit Route.

news.title: Maharashtra govt panel proposes 10% extra carpet area for housing societies going for self-redevelopment
news.para: Mumbai residents may soon get more space in self-redeveloped homes. A government committee suggests a 10% increase in carpet area. This encourages residents to redevelop their buildings independently. The scheme could extend to cluster redevelopment projects. Slum dwellers are also included in the proposal. The government is considering financial support for these projects.

news.title: China Vanke expects up to $1.7 billion net loss in H1 2025
news.para: China Vanke, a state-backed property developer, anticipates a significant net loss. The expected loss is up to 12 billion yuan for the first half of the year. This is due to a drop in project settlements and low profit margins. The company is also making extra provisions. Vanke had a senior management reshuffle earlier this year.

news.title: China's new home prices in June fall at fastest monthly pace in eight months
news.para: New data reveals that China's home prices declined in June. This is the fastest monthly drop in eight months. The property sector continues to weigh on economic growth. Policymakers are struggling to revive demand. The State Council plans a nationwide survey of land and projects. Current support measures include easing restrictions and reducing mortgage rates.

news.title: Illegal constructions will not be spared, strict action against erring officials: Maharashtra deputy CM
news.para: Maharashtra government is committed to cracking down on illegal constructions, Deputy CM Eknath Shinde affirmed in the assembly. Instructions will be issued to the BMC to list unauthorized structures, and officials found complicit will face strict action. Demolition drives, paused due to monsoon, will resume, with action taken under the MRTP Act.

news.title: Smartworks Coworking Spaces IPO gets subscribed 13.45 times
news.para: Smartworks Coworking Spaces' Rs 583-crore IPO witnessed a robust 13.45 times subscription on its final day, driven by strong QIB and NII interest. The company plans to utilize the raised capital for expansion, debt reduction, and general corporate purposes. With 48 operational co-working centers, Smartworks aims to strengthen its position as a leading flexible office space provider.

news.title: Charles Group, Patel Family Office Sign $1 Billion Real Estate Pact at Global Wealth Conference
news.para: Charles Group and Patel Family Office signed a $1 billion agreement at the Global Wealth Conference 2025 to co-develop a digital investment platform. The platform will focus on real estate and infrastructure assets across the UK, GCC, India, and the SAARC region. This partnership aims to create accessible, transparent, and scalable investment opportunities for SWFs, family offices, and institutional buyers.

news.title: ED files second supplementary complaint against Unitech Group promoters in money laundering case
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) has filed a second supplementary complaint against Ramesh Chandra and others, including several companies, for money laundering involving Unitech Limited. The investigation revealed that approximately ₹7,794.35 crore was siphoned off from ₹16,075.89 crore collected from homebuyers. Funds were diverted through fraudulent methods and complex international layering, with proceeds used to purchase personal assets abroad.

news.title: Kochi corporation faces heat over missing building data in K-Smart portal
news.para: Kochi Corporation faces a data crisis with approximately 50,000 building permits missing from its database, disrupting tax payments and license renewals. The issue arose after a contract dispute with TCS led to withheld data during the e-governance program transition. Opposition leaders criticize the administration for failing to identify discrepancies, leaving property owners struggling with omitted building numbers and payment issues.

news.title: Settlement officials dismissed after investigation into fraudulent plot allocations in Jaisalmer
news.para: In Jaisalmer, four officials faced dismissal due to a land allocation scam. The Settlement Commissioner took action after an investigation in Ram Nagar. The probe revealed fraudulent activities dating back to 2006. Officials allocated plots meant for 2006 in 2016, causing a loss of Rs 5 crore. The Anti-Corruption Bureau is reviewing cases.

news.title: Prayagraj to get 800 homestay-cum-B&B units under new tourism policy
news.para: Prayagraj introduces a new Bread & Breakfast cum Homestay policy. This policy aims to improve accommodation for pilgrims and tourists. The initiative replaces the Paying Guest policy. It focuses on providing safe and high-quality stays. The tourism department plans to establish 800 homestay units. Registered units must meet specific safety standards. Applications are submitted online and reviewed by a committee.

news.title: Two unsafe Margao buildings to be razed after 1.5-year delay
news.para: After prolonged delays and legal challenges, the demolition of the unsafe 'Cabecca de Calconde' building in Margao is imminent, following a collector's order prompted by public safety concerns. The PWD has shortlisted agencies for the demolition, pending the final vacation of occupants and resolution of a high court matter. Concerns linger regarding potential redevelopment plans after demolition.

news.title: Land registration freeze continues over ‘tampered’ records in Andhra Pradesh
news.para: The Andhra Pradesh government is struggling to resolve the free-hold lands issue, with registration of 20 lakh acres of assigned lands on hold due to suspected record tampering. Farmers are unable to sell their lands, and despite a GoM's efforts, a solution remains elusive.

news.title: DTPE issues notices to 61 plot owners in Sushant Lok-1 for running illegal commercial activities
news.para: Gurugram authorities have taken strict action against commercial establishments operating illegally in residential areas of Sushant Lok-1. A recent enforcement drive resulted in 61 show-cause notices issued to plot owners and the sealing of unauthorized constructions in Vyapar Kendra Market.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh launches self-certification scheme to streamline building permissions
news.para: Andhra Pradesh government introduced new rules for building approvals. The Self-Certification Scheme 2025 aims to simplify the process. It allows instant online permissions for construction. Licensed professionals ensure compliance with regulations.

news.title: Rampant building violations continue unchecked in Bengaluru as officials cite lack of resources
news.para: Bengaluru's Cooke Town is grappling with rampant building violations. Builders flout norms, adding floors and ignoring setbacks. Despite Supreme Court guidelines, BBMP is slow to act. Residents allege negligence and inaction, even with demolition notices issued. Only token action is taken against violators. Residents fear the situation will worsen, straining infrastructure and blocking pedestrian access.
